G isnt there yet Right now, theres no such thing as a G phone that supports all the G bands and technologies that carriers and device makers ultimately want. Qualcomm is still on its first generation G modem, and companies like Samsung are making headway of their own. But a multirung strategy that factors in low , mid , and high band spectrum is crucial to making G connectivity feel whole, and none of the devices on the market currently will be able to meet that vision when the carriers pursuing it are ready. By next September, Qualcomm will almost certainly have introduced a more capable and future proofed G modem that will better unlock all the potential we keep hearing about. But this first wave of G devices is not that.
